---
import BasicLayout from "../layouts/BasicLayout.astro";
---

<BasicLayout
  title="Projects"
  description="Personal and research projects across AI, robotics, and signal processing."
  page="projects"
>
  <main class="px-4 pb-20 pt-80 md:px-8 lg:px-16">
    <!-- Back button (top-right) -->
    <a
      class="absolute top-15 right-20 text-white bg-neutral-900 hover:bg-neutral-800 px-4 py-2 border border-neutral-600 rounded-lg inline-flex items-center gap-2"
      href="/"
    >
      Back
    </a>

    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-white mb-10">
      Projects
    </h1>

    <!-- Research projects section (TOP) -->
    <h3 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-300 mb-4">
      Research Projects
    </h3>

    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 mb-16">
      <!-- MPhil: Speech-to-Speech Dialogue Benchmarking -->
      <section class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-700 bg-neutral-900/60 p-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">
            Speech-to-Speech Dialogue Benchmarking &amp; Robustness
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400">
            MPhil Research Project · University of Cambridge · 2025–2026
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-neutral-200 space-y-2">
          <li>Benchmarked speech-to-speech dialogue systems, analysing cross-modal error propagation across ASR, language modelling, and TTS components.</li>
          <li>Conducted multilingual and speaker-level evaluations to identify performance disparities linked to language variation and sociolinguistic attributes.</li>
          <li>Designed and evaluated modality alignment improvements to speech-native pipelines to enhance robustness and spoken response quality.</li>
          <li>Developed a reproducible evaluation framework combining automatic metrics and controlled A/B testing for system comparison.</li>
          <li>Analysed failure modes in cascaded and speech-native architectures to inform engineering interventions and future model design.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- FYP: Digital Twin Robotic Waste Sorting -->
      <section class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-700 bg-neutral-900/60 p-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">
            Digital Twin Robotic Waste Sorting
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400">
            Final Year Project · NTU · 2024–2025
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-neutral-200 space-y-2">
          <li>Developed a digital twin of a robotic arm in Unity, synchronised in real time with the physical robot via UDP, OPC&nbsp;UA and an OpenCR controller.</li>
          <li>Implemented a PPO-based deep RL framework in TensorFlow for autonomous pick-and-place of coloured waste objects.</li>
          <li>Trained for ≈2.5M steps with reward shaping and environment randomisation, achieving ~70% testing accuracy.</li>
          <li>Designed evaluation scenarios to probe robustness and failure modes against scripted baselines.</li>
          <li>Documented the full pipeline from hardware configuration to simulation, training, and deployment.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- URECA: HRV Signal Processing & ML -->
      <section class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-700 bg-neutral-900/60 p-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">
            HRV Signal Analysis &amp; Classification
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400">
            URECA Research Project · NTU · 2022–2023
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-neutral-200 space-y-2">
          <li>Designed a signal-processing pipeline for HRV including band-pass filtering, normalisation and peak detection.</li>
          <li>Computed RMSSD-based statistics and geometric features such as convex hull area and Mahalanobis distance area.</li>
          <li>Trained a random forest classifier to detect abnormal HRV patterns, achieving ~94.4% accuracy.</li>
          <li>Analysed feature importance to understand which metrics contributed most to model performance.</li>
          <li>Summarised findings to support future work on physiological signal analysis.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>

    <!-- Personal project section (BOTTOM) -->
    <h3 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-300 mb-4">
      Personal Project
    </h3>

    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <!-- Finance News Sentiment Analysis -->
      <section class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-700 bg-neutral-900/60 p-5 flex flex-col gap-2">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">
            Finance News Sentiment Analysis
          </h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400">
            Personal Project · 2025–Present
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-neutral-200 space-y-2">
          <li>Built an NLP pipeline with LangChain to ingest, preprocess and analyse financial news headlines and articles.</li>
          <li>Used Hugging Face models for sentiment classification and embeddings focused on market-relevant language.</li>
          <li>Experimented with vector databases to enable semantic search and retrieval over news streams.</li>
          <li>Explored simple ways to relate sentiment signals to tickers and basic trading heuristics as a starting point.</li>
          <li>Structured the project so individual components (scraper, embedder, model) can be swapped or upgraded easily.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-neutral-300">
          GitHub:&nbsp;
          <a
            href="#"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="underline text-blue-300"
          >
            On going
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</BasicLayout>
